{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Images like this, from the Auschwitz concentration camp,"},{"time":4000,"text":"have been seared into our consciousness during the twentieth century"},{"time":9000,"text":"and have given us a new understanding of who we are,"},{"time":14000,"text":"where we've come from and the times we live in."},{"time":17000,"text":"During the twentieth century, we witnessed the atrocities"},{"time":21000,"text":"of Stalin, Hitler, Mao, Pol Pot, Rwanda and other genocides,"},{"time":26000,"text":"and even though the twenty-first century is only seven years old,"},{"time":30000,"text":"we have already witnessed an ongoing genocide in Darfur"},{"time":34000,"text":"and the daily horrors of Iraq."},{"time":37000,"text":"This has led to a common understanding of our situation,"},{"time":40000,"text":"namely that modernity has brought us terrible violence, and perhaps"},{"time":44000,"text":"that native peoples lived in a state of harmony that we have departed from, to our peril."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47000,"text":"Here is an example"},{"time":52000,"text":"from an op-ed on Thanksgiving, in the Boston Globe"},{"time":55000,"text":"a couple of years ago, where the writer wrote, \"The Indian life"},{"time":59000,"text":"was a difficult one, but there were no employment problems,"},{"time":62000,"text":"community harmony was strong, substance abuse unknown,"},{"time":65000,"text":"crime nearly non-existent, what warfare there was between tribes"},{"time":69000,"text":"was largely ritualistic and seldom resulted in indiscriminate"},{"time":72000,"text":"or wholesale slaughter.\" Now, you're all familiar with this treacle."},{"time":77000,"text":"We teach it to our children. We hear it on television"},{"time":80000,"text":"and in storybooks. Now, the original title of this session"},{"time":85000,"text":"was, \"Everything You Know Is Wrong,\" and I'm going to present evidence"},{"time":88000,"text":"that this particular part of our common understanding is wrong,"},{"time":91000,"text":"that, in fact, our ancestors were far more violent than we are,"},{"time":95000,"text":"that violence has been in decline for long stretches of time,"},{"time":99000,"text":"and that today we are probably living in the most peaceful time in our species' existence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102000,"text":"Now, in the decade of Darfur and Iraq,"},{"time":107000,"text":"a statement like that might seem somewhere between hallucinatory"},{"time":110000,"text":"and obscene. But I'm going to try to convince you"},{"time":113000,"text":"that that is the correct picture. The decline of violence"},{"time":119000,"text":"is a fractal phenomenon. You can see it over millennia,"},{"time":122000,"text":"over centuries, over decades and over years,"},{"time":126000,"text":"although there seems to have been a tipping point at the onset"},{"time":128000,"text":"of the Age of Reason in the sixteenth century. One sees it"},{"time":132000,"text":"all over the world, although not homogeneously."},{"time":136000,"text":"It's especially evident in the West, beginning with England"},{"time":139000,"text":"and Holland around the time of the Enlightenment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142000,"text":"Let me take you on a journey of several powers of 10 --"},{"time":146000,"text":"from the millennium scale to the year scale --"},{"time":148000,"text":"to try to persuade you of this. Until 10,000 years ago, all humans"},{"time":152000,"text":"lived as hunter-gatherers, without permanent settlements"},{"time":155000,"text":"or government. And this is the state that's commonly thought"},{"time":158000,"text":"to be one of primordial harmony. But the archaeologist"},{"time":164000,"text":"Lawrence Keeley, looking at casualty rates"},{"time":168000,"text":"among contemporary hunter-gatherers, which is our best source"},{"time":172000,"text":"of evidence about this way of life, has shown a rather different conclusion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178000,"text":"Here is a graph that he put together"},{"time":180000,"text":"showing the percentage of male deaths due to warfare"},{"time":183000,"text":"in a number of foraging, or hunting and gathering societies."},{"time":188000,"text":"The red bars correspond to the likelihood that a man will die"},{"time":194000,"text":"at the hands of another man, as opposed to passing away"},{"time":197000,"text":"of natural causes, in a variety of foraging societies"},{"time":201000,"text":"in the New Guinea Highlands and the Amazon Rainforest."},{"time":205000,"text":"And they range from a rate of almost a 60 percent chance that a man will die"},{"time":208000,"text":"at the hands of another man to, in the case of the Gebusi,"},{"time":212000,"text":"only a 15 percent chance. The tiny, little blue bar in the lower"},{"time":216000,"text":"left-hand corner plots the corresponding statistic from United States"},{"time":220000,"text":"and Europe in the twentieth century, and includes all the deaths"},{"time":224000,"text":"of both World Wars. If the death rate in tribal warfare had prevailed"},{"time":229000,"text":"during the 20th century, there would have been two billion deaths rather than 100 million."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235000,"text":"Also at the millennium scale, we can look"},{"time":238000,"text":"at the way of life of early civilizations such as the ones described"},{"time":243000,"text":"in the Bible. And in this supposed source of our moral values,"},{"time":248000,"text":"one can read descriptions of what was expected in warfare,"},{"time":252000,"text":"such as the following from Numbers 31: \"And they warred"},{"time":255000,"text":"against the Midianites as the Lord commanded Moses,"},{"time":258000,"text":"and they slew all the males. And Moses said unto them,"},{"time":261000,"text":"'Have you saved all the women alive? Now, therefore, kill every male"},{"time":265000,"text":"among the little ones and kill every woman that hath known man"},{"time":268000,"text":"by lying with him, but all the women children that have not know a man"},{"time":272000,"text":"by lying with him keep alive for yourselves.'\" In other words,"},{"time":275000,"text":"kill the men; kill the children; if you see any virgins,"},{"time":280000,"text":"then you can keep them alive so that you can rape them."},{"time":283000,"text":"You can find four or five passages in the Bible of this ilk."},{"time":287000,"text":"Also in the Bible, one sees that the death penalty"},{"time":290000,"text":"was the accepted punishment for crimes such as homosexuality,"},{"time":295000,"text":"adultery, blasphemy, idolatry, talking back to your parents --"},{"time":299000,"text":"(Laughter) -- and picking up sticks on the Sabbath."},{"time":303000,"text":"Well, let's click the zoom lens"},{"time":306000,"text":"down one order of magnitude, and look at the century scale."},{"time":309000,"text":"Although we don't have statistics for warfare throughout"},{"time":314000,"text":"the Middle Ages to modern times,"},{"time":315000,"text":"we know just from conventional history -- the evidence"},{"time":318000,"text":"was under our nose all along that there has been a reduction"},{"time":322000,"text":"in socially sanctioned forms of violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325000,"text":"For example, any social history will reveal that mutilation and torture"},{"time":329000,"text":"were routine forms of criminal punishment. The kind of infraction"},{"time":332000,"text":"today that would give you a fine, in those days would result in"},{"time":336000,"text":"your tongue being cut out, your ears being cut off, you being blinded,"},{"time":340000,"text":"a hand being chopped off and so on."},{"time":342000,"text":"There were numerous ingenious forms of sadistic capital punishment:"},{"time":347000,"text":"burning at the stake, disemboweling, breaking on the wheel,"},{"time":350000,"text":"being pulled apart by horses and so on."},{"time":353000,"text":"The death penalty was a sanction for a long list of non-violent crimes:"},{"time":357000,"text":"criticizing the king, stealing a loaf of bread. Slavery, of course,"},{"time":362000,"text":"was the preferred labor-saving device, and cruelty was"},{"time":366000,"text":"a popular form of entertainment. Perhaps the most vivid example"},{"time":369000,"text":"was the practice of cat burning, in which a cat was hoisted"},{"time":372000,"text":"on a stage and lowered in a sling into a fire,"},{"time":375000,"text":"and the spectators shrieked in laughter as the cat, howling in pain,"},{"time":381000,"text":"was burned to death."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383000,"text":"What about one-on-one murder? Well, there, there are good statistics,"},{"time":386000,"text":"because many municipalities recorded the cause of death."},{"time":392000,"text":"The criminologist Manuel Eisner"},{"time":397000,"text":"scoured all of the historical records across Europe"},{"time":399000,"text":"for homicide rates in any village, hamlet, town, county"},{"time":404000,"text":"that he could find, and he supplemented them"},{"time":406000,"text":"with national data, when nations started keeping statistics."},{"time":410000,"text":"He plotted on a logarithmic scale, going from 100 deaths"},{"time":417000,"text":"per 100,000 people per year, which was approximately the rate"},{"time":423000,"text":"of homicide in the Middle Ages. And the figure plummets down"},{"time":428000,"text":"to less than one homicide per 100,000 people per year"},{"time":433000,"text":"in seven or eight European countries. Then, there is a slight uptick"},{"time":437000,"text":"in the 1960s. The people who said that rock 'n' roll would lead"},{"time":441000,"text":"to the decline of moral values actually had a grain of truth to that."},{"time":445000,"text":"But there was a decline from at least two orders of magnitude"},{"time":449000,"text":"in homicide from the Middle Ages to the present,"},{"time":452000,"text":"and the elbow occurred in the early sixteenth century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457000,"text":"Let's click down now to the decade scale."},{"time":459000,"text":"According to non-governmental organizations"},{"time":462000,"text":"that keep such statistics, since 1945, in Europe and the Americas,"},{"time":466000,"text":"there has been a steep decline in interstate wars,"},{"time":470000,"text":"in deadly ethnic riots or pogroms, and in military coups,"},{"time":474000,"text":"even in South America. Worldwide, there's been a steep decline"},{"time":478000,"text":"in deaths in interstate wars. The yellow bars here show the number"},{"time":484000,"text":"of deaths per war per year from 1950 to the present."},{"time":489000,"text":"And, as you can see, the death rate goes down from 65,000 deaths"},{"time":493000,"text":"per conflict per year in the 1950s to less than 2,000 deaths"},{"time":497000,"text":"per conflict per year in this decade, as horrific as it is."},{"time":501000,"text":"Even in the year scale, one can see a decline of violence."},{"time":505000,"text":"Since the end of the Cold War, there have been fewer civil wars,"},{"time":508000,"text":"fewer genocides -- indeed, a 90 percent reduction since post-World War II highs --"},{"time":514000,"text":"and even a reversal of the 1960s uptick in homicide and violent crime."},{"time":520000,"text":"This is from the FBI Uniform Crime Statistics. You can see"},{"time":524000,"text":"that there is a fairly low rate of violence in the '50s and the '60s,"},{"time":528000,"text":"then it soared upward for several decades, and began"},{"time":532000,"text":"a precipitous decline, starting in the 1990s, so that it went back"},{"time":536000,"text":"to the level that was last enjoyed in 1960."},{"time":540000,"text":"President Clinton, if you're here, thank you."},{"time":542000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":544000,"text":"So the question is, why are so many people so wrong"},{"time":547000,"text":"about something so important? I think there are a number of reasons."},{"time":551000,"text":"One of them is we have better reporting. The Associated Press"},{"time":554000,"text":"is a better chronicler of wars over the surface of the Earth"},{"time":558000,"text":"than sixteenth-century monks were."},{"time":562000,"text":"There's a cognitive illusion. We cognitive psychologists know that the easier it is"},{"time":567000,"text":"to recall specific instances of something,"},{"time":570000,"text":"the higher the probability that you assign to it."},{"time":573000,"text":"Things that we read about in the paper with gory footage"},{"time":577000,"text":"burn into memory more than reports of a lot more people dying"},{"time":581000,"text":"in their beds of old age. There are dynamics in the opinion"},{"time":587000,"text":"and advocacy markets: no one ever attracted observers, advocates"},{"time":592000,"text":"and donors by saying"},{"time":594000,"text":"things just seem to be getting better and better."},{"time":596000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":597000,"text":"There's guilt about our treatment of native peoples"},{"time":600000,"text":"in modern intellectual life, and an unwillingness to acknowledge"},{"time":603000,"text":"there could be anything good about Western culture."},{"time":606000,"text":"And of course, our change in standards can outpace the change"},{"time":611000,"text":"in behavior. One of the reasons violence went down"},{"time":614000,"text":"is that people got sick of the carnage and cruelty in their time."},{"time":617000,"text":"That's a process that seems to be continuing,"},{"time":620000,"text":"but if it outstrips behavior by the standards of the day,"},{"time":624000,"text":"things always look more barbaric than they would have been"},{"time":627000,"text":"by historic standards. So today, we get exercised -- and rightly so --"},{"time":631000,"text":"if a handful of murderers get executed by lethal injection"},{"time":637000,"text":"in Texas after a 15-year appeal process. We don't consider"},{"time":642000,"text":"that a couple of hundred years ago, they may have been burned"},{"time":645000,"text":"at the stake for criticizing the king after a trial"},{"time":648000,"text":"that lasted 10 minutes, and indeed, that that would have been repeated"},{"time":651000,"text":"over and over again. Today, we look at capital punishment"},{"time":656000,"text":"as evidence of how low our behavior can sink,"},{"time":659000,"text":"rather than how high our standards have risen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663000,"text":"Well, why has violence declined? No one really knows,"},{"time":666000,"text":"but I have read four explanations, all of which, I think,"},{"time":671000,"text":"have some grain of plausibility. The first is, maybe"},{"time":674000,"text":"Thomas Hobbes got it right. He was the one who said"},{"time":677000,"text":"that life in a state of nature was \"solitary, poor, nasty, brutish"},{"time":682000,"text":"and short.\" Not because, he argued,"},{"time":686000,"text":"humans have some primordial thirst for blood"},{"time":689000,"text":"or aggressive instinct or territorial imperative,"},{"time":693000,"text":"but because of the logic of anarchy. In a state of anarchy,"},{"time":696000,"text":"there's a constant temptation to invade your neighbors preemptively,"},{"time":700000,"text":"before they invade you. More recently, Thomas Schelling"},{"time":703000,"text":"gives the analogy of a homeowner who hears a rustling"},{"time":706000,"text":"in the basement. Being a good American, he has a pistol"},{"time":708000,"text":"in the nightstand, pulls out his gun, and walks down the stairs."},{"time":712000,"text":"And what does he see but a burglar with a gun in his hand."},{"time":715000,"text":"Now, each one of them is thinking,"},{"time":716000,"text":"\"I don't really want to kill that guy, but he's about to kill me."},{"time":720000,"text":"Maybe I had better shoot him, before he shoots me,"},{"time":724000,"text":"especially since, even if he doesn't want to kill me,"},{"time":726000,"text":"he's probably worrying right now that I might kill him"},{"time":729000,"text":"before he kills me.\" And so on."},{"time":732000,"text":"Hunter-gatherer peoples explicitly go through this train of thought,"},{"time":737000,"text":"and will often raid their neighbors out of fear of being raided first."}]},{"cues":[{"time":742000,"text":"Now, one way of dealing with this problem is by deterrence."},{"time":745000,"text":"You don't strike first, but you have a publicly announced policy"},{"time":750000,"text":"that you will retaliate savagely if you are invaded."},{"time":753000,"text":"The only thing is that it's"},{"time":755000,"text":"liable to having its bluff called, and therefore can only work"},{"time":760000,"text":"if it's credible. To make it credible, you must avenge all insults"},{"time":765000,"text":"and settle all scores, which leads to the cycles of bloody vendetta."},{"time":769000,"text":"Life becomes an episode of \"The Sopranos.\" Hobbes' solution,"},{"time":774000,"text":"the \"Leviathan,\" was that if authority for the legitimate use"},{"time":778000,"text":"of violence was vested in a single democratic agency -- a leviathan --"},{"time":784000,"text":"then such a state can reduce the temptation of attack,"},{"time":787000,"text":"because any kind of aggression will be punished,"},{"time":790000,"text":"leaving its profitability as zero. That would remove the temptation"},{"time":795000,"text":"to invade preemptively, out of fear of them attacking you first."},{"time":799000,"text":"It removes the need for a hair trigger for retaliation"},{"time":803000,"text":"to make your deterrent threat credible. And therefore, it would lead"},{"time":806000,"text":"to a state of peace. Eisner -- the man who plotted the homicide rates"},{"time":812000,"text":"that you failed to see in the earlier slide --"},{"time":815000,"text":"argued that the timing of the decline of homicide in Europe"},{"time":819000,"text":"coincided with the rise of centralized states."},{"time":823000,"text":"So that's a bit of a support for the leviathan theory."},{"time":826000,"text":"Also supporting it is the fact that we today see eruptions of violence"},{"time":830000,"text":"in zones of anarchy, in failed states, collapsed empires,"},{"time":834000,"text":"frontier regions, mafias, street gangs and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840000,"text":"The second explanation is that in many times and places,"},{"time":843000,"text":"there is a widespread sentiment that life is cheap."},{"time":847000,"text":"In earlier times, when suffering and early death were common"},{"time":851000,"text":"in one's own life, one has fewer compunctions about inflicting them"},{"time":855000,"text":"on others. And as technology and economic efficiency make life"},{"time":859000,"text":"longer and more pleasant, one puts a higher value on life in general."},{"time":863000,"text":"This was an argument from the political scientist James Payne."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867000,"text":"A third explanation invokes the concept of a nonzero-sum game,"},{"time":871000,"text":"and was worked out in the book \"Nonzero\" by the journalist"},{"time":875000,"text":"Robert Wright. Wright points out that in certain circumstances,"},{"time":879000,"text":"cooperation or non-violence can benefit both parties"},{"time":882000,"text":"in an interaction, such as gains in trade when two parties trade"},{"time":888000,"text":"their surpluses and both come out ahead, or when two parties"},{"time":892000,"text":"lay down their arms and split the so-called peace dividend"},{"time":895000,"text":"that results in them not having to fight the whole time."},{"time":899000,"text":"Wright argues that technology has increased the number"},{"time":901000,"text":"of positive-sum games that humans tend to be embroiled in,"},{"time":906000,"text":"by allowing the trade of goods, services and ideas"},{"time":909000,"text":"over longer distances and among larger groups of people."},{"time":913000,"text":"The result is that other people become more valuable alive than dead,"},{"time":916000,"text":"and violence declines for selfish reasons. As Wright put it,"},{"time":922000,"text":"\"Among the many reasons that I think that we should not bomb"},{"time":924000,"text":"the Japanese is that they built my mini-van.\""},{"time":927000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":929000,"text":"The fourth explanation is captured in the title of a book"},{"time":933000,"text":"called \"The Expanding Circle,\" by the philosopher Peter Singer,"},{"time":937000,"text":"who argues that evolution bequeathed humans with a sense"},{"time":940000,"text":"of empathy, an ability to treat other peoples' interests"},{"time":945000,"text":"as comparable to one's own. Unfortunately, by default"},{"time":949000,"text":"we apply it only to a very narrow circle of friends and family."},{"time":953000,"text":"People outside that circle are treated as sub-human,"},{"time":956000,"text":"and can be exploited with impunity. But, over history,"},{"time":960000,"text":"the circle has expanded. One can see, in historical record,"},{"time":964000,"text":"it expanding from the village, to the clan, to the tribe,"},{"time":968000,"text":"to the nation, to other races, to both sexes,"},{"time":971000,"text":"and, in Singer's own arguments, something that we should extend"},{"time":973000,"text":"to other sentient species. The question is,"},{"time":978000,"text":"if this has happened, what has powered that expansion?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":981000,"text":"And there are a number of possibilities, such as increasing circles"},{"time":984000,"text":"of reciprocity in the sense that Robert Wright argues for."},{"time":989000,"text":"The logic of the golden rule -- the more you think about and interact"},{"time":993000,"text":"with other people, the more you realize that it is untenable"},{"time":997000,"text":"to privilege your interests over theirs,"},{"time":1001000,"text":"at least not if you want them to listen to you. You can't say"},{"time":1004000,"text":"that my interests are special compared to yours,"},{"time":1007000,"text":"anymore than you can say that the particular spot"},{"time":1010000,"text":"that I'm standing on is a unique part of the universe"},{"time":1013000,"text":"because I happen to be standing on it that very minute."},{"time":1016000,"text":"It may also be powered by cosmopolitanism, by histories,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"and journalism, and memoirs, and realistic fiction, and travel,"},{"time":1024000,"text":"and literacy, which allows you to project yourself into the lives"},{"time":1028000,"text":"of other people that formerly you may have treated as sub-human,"},{"time":1032000,"text":"and also to realize the accidental contingency of your own station"},{"time":1036000,"text":"in life, the sense that \"there but for fortune go I.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1041000,"text":"Whatever its causes, the decline of violence, I think,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"has profound implications. It should force us to ask not just, why"},{"time":1048000,"text":"is there war? But also, why is there peace? Not just,"},{"time":1053000,"text":"what are we doing wrong? But also, what have we been doing right?"},{"time":1057000,"text":"Because we have been doing something right,"},{"time":1059000,"text":"and it sure would be good to find out what it is."},{"time":1061000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":1062000,"text":"(Applause)."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1073000,"text":"Chris Anderson: I loved that talk. I think a lot of people here in the room would say"},{"time":1077000,"text":"that that expansion of -- that you were talking about,"},{"time":1080000,"text":"that Peter Singer talks about, is also driven by, just by technology,"},{"time":1083000,"text":"by greater visibility of the other, and the sense that the world"},{"time":1087000,"text":"is therefore getting smaller. I mean, is that also a grain of truth?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1091000,"text":"Steven Pinker: Very much. It would fit both in Wright's theory,"},{"time":1095000,"text":"that it allows us to enjoy the benefits of cooperation"},{"time":1099000,"text":"over larger and larger circles. But also, I think it helps us"},{"time":1104000,"text":"imagine what it's like to be someone else. I think when you read"},{"time":1107000,"text":"these horrific tortures that were common in the Middle Ages, you think,"},{"time":1110000,"text":"how could they possibly have done it,"},{"time":1112000,"text":"how could they have not have empathized with the person"},{"time":1115000,"text":"that they're disemboweling? But clearly,"},{"time":1118000,"text":"as far as they're concerned, this is just an alien being"},{"time":1121000,"text":"that does not have feelings akin to their own. Anything, I think,"},{"time":1124000,"text":"that makes it easier to imagine trading places"},{"time":1127000,"text":"with someone else means that it increases your moral consideration"},{"time":1130000,"text":"to that other person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1131000,"text":"CA: Well, Steve, I would love every news media owner to hear that talk"},{"time":1135000,"text":"at some point in the next year. I think it's really important. Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1137000,"text":"SP: My pleasure."}]}]}